It is with a heavy heart we announce the passing of one of our veteran brothers, Rob McGowan. Rob served as a supply tech from 2003-2020, father to 3 children, V4F member #008 and part of the V4F Atlantic team. Rob supported the truckers in their fight for freedom in Ottawa, attended Rolling Thunder Ottawa 2022 and was actively involved in the veteran community in Fredericton, New Brunswick. Rob lost the fight with his personal demons but he will not be forgotten. Rolling Thunder Ottawa 2023 will be dedicated to Rob. For those who are able to make it, there will be a celebration of life on 5 August 2023 at 1300 (1pm) at New River Beach, NB. Hope to see you there. Rest in peace brother.

url_description: The Public Order Inquiry Commission began public hearings October 14, exactly eight months after the declaration of a state of emergency by Prime Minister Justin Trudeau‚Äôs government. Let‚Äôs recall that the Trudeau government claimed that the Freedom Convoy protests in Ottawa were so dangerous that they imperilled public safety and this necessitated the use of draconian and emergency powers, that have only once been previously invoked in peacetime. The hearings give us an opportunity to test Trudeau‚Äôs claim, and so far the government‚Äôs rationale has all but fallen flat on its face. Of course, there could be remarkable revelations in the future which put a different cast on the events, but so far, a range of witnesses give reason to be highly skeptical of the government‚Äôs rationale and the narrative that fuelled it.

EYEWITNESS TO DECEIT ‚Äì PM Trudeau's Info War on Freedom Convoy 2022 The book describes how Prime Minister Trudeau launched a fifth-generation style information war against Freedom Convoy 2022. The book was written by Veterans 4 Freedom members Tom Quiggin and Rick Gill. It is dedicated to V4F member Corporal Chris Deering who was the sole survivor of an IED attack on an armoured vehicle in Afghanistan. The book is also dedicated to Corporal Thomas Hamilton, Private John Curwin, and Private Justin Jones of who died in the attack. The preface, which discusses the situation of V4F member Jeremy MacKenzie, was written by former RCMP Corporal Danny Bulford. Tom Quiggin worked within Freedom Convoy 2022 in an intelligence support role. From that position, he was able to observe how the Prime Minister, several cabinet ministers and the mainstream media started a campaign of deceit against the convoy before it even arrived. A variety of specific lies are exposed such as the fake claims about an arson attack, guns in the trucks and claims of rape. It also addresses the issue of fake claims of Russian support by the CBC and their stories about ‚Äúmissing money.‚Äù The book also details how the campaign of lies has been exposed since the convoy. It provides multiple examples of how the politicians, police and media have been caught out. The book is available in paperback or Kindle at https://tinyurl.com/yfnykfr8

The power of bartering and exchange of services is very real. It's something that should be placed on higher emphasis as we move away from corrupted systems and move towards self sufficiency and communities. A couch set turned into a two night stay at a cottage in Tobermory, that led to connecting with the owner. A like minded, new friend, that shared their view over Georgian Bay and this amazing sauna! All because of a used couch set that would be delivered straight to the property. The opportunities are endless when we think of all the skills, resources, services and unique value we all have. Everyone has something to offer, even if you think you don't. We started with just offering up our truck for services. We didn't know what life would like look, how we'd get by or make a means to survive. We knew we were convicted in our stance and what we were not willing to compromise on, which actually made making decisions easier. Lots of changes were made such as downsizing, homeschooling, and entrepreneurship. Life isn't exactly how we thought it would be or planned on. But that's the beauty of it, life is always changing and evolving and we should be able to grow, change, adapt and evolve with it. You never know, it may just end up leading you to exactly where you're meant to be and completely different than what you thought, and maybe that's a good thing. Maybe that's the gift of the last 2yrs to completely change us as individuals, society, creating deeper connections and communities, and leading us to a way of life that is how we were always meant to live. Maybe its a story you're meant to tell, a missing piece in the puzzle. Maybe there's a greater reason yet to be discovered. There's lots of work, healing and hardship to overcome, but I'm still optimistic for the future and the that many are creating for our future generations. Share your skills/resources below...lets make some connections and grow communities!

url_title: Russian Godfathers (Full Doc)
url_description: This documentary series examines the relationship between Russia's richest men ('the oligarchs') and Putin's administration in the Kremlin. The series follows each one in turn to find out what they were up to in the years leading up to 2005, and the crew is granted intimate access. Two of the five are now in exile, wanted on criminal charges and planning their own anti-Putin campaigns with their wealth and influence. 1) The Fugitive 00:00:00 Broadcast a year before the Litvinenko murder, this fascinating series lifted the lid on the struggle that still continues between Putin, and his adversaries, the Russian Oligarchs. The first part follows exile and Litvenenko associate Boris Berezovsky as he campaigns to fight Putin in the Media and along Russia's borders. Under threat of arrest, Berezovsky travels to revolutionary Ukraine for the campaign to elect Yuschenko. 2) The Prisoner 00:59:15 This part follows the trial and conviction of Russia's richest man, Mikhail Khodorkovsky. Khodorkovsky's grinning face was famously beamed across the world from behind the bars of the court's cage, and this episode reveals the tactics that Putin used to suppress the oil baron and separate him from his company and wealth. 3) The Politician 01:58:45 Final part in the formidable series on Putin's fight with the oligarchs. Shot a year before the murder of Litvinenko, this film examines Putin's fight with the only serious rival for the presidency, Yuri Luzhkov. The crew follow Luzhkov, the renegade billionaire Mayor of Moscow as he takes the fight to Putin. This is a fascinating film which shows both the ruthless methods in which Putin crushes his opposition and the extreme corruption that exist at the highest levels of Russian government. --- #IMMORTALUPLOADS ---

url_description: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau suggested on Monday that while protests surrounding Parliament Hill in Ottawa have mostly dispersed and the horns are no longer sounding, the work to heal the pandemic divisions in the country that the convoy exposed must now begin. He made the comments ahead of a vote by MPs on the invocation of the Emergencies Act, which would be revoked if that vote fails. Trudeau that the Emergencies Act would not be revoked yet as the "state of emergency is not over." There are concerns over the coming days‚Äã, he said Public Safety Minister Marco Mendicino added that the government has seen reports of "potential activity" in the Ottawa area and need‚Äãs to remain "vigilant" to further ‚Äãpotential blockades. The act will lift 30 days after it was invoked, so about mid-March, unless another vote is taken to extend it. Finance Minister Chrystia Freeland said Monday that people need to be "very, very careful‚Äã" to get ‚Äãthe "facts exactly right" regarding the Emergencies Act. She spoke about two Conservative MPs who claim constituents donated small amounts to the so-called "Freedom Convoy" and had their accounts frozen. She countered that at no time, did the RCMP provide a list of donors to Financial Institutions. She said that, according to the RCMP, the police force did provide names of organizers and leaders of the protests and of people whose trucks were "part of occupations and blockades" to financial institutions. She added the measures only applied as of Feb. 15. The vote on the act is expected to pass when MPs vote at approximately 8 p.m. ET, with the NDP voicing its support for the act. The Conservatives and Bloc Qu√©becois have said they would vote against the motion. If the motion fails, however, the act and all powers stemming from it would be torn up. If it passes, they will remain in place until mid-March at the latest.
